title: [Medicine] Pfizer-BioNTech booster shots reduce the chance of confirmed infection by a factor of 11.3 and reduce the chances of severe infection by a factor of 19.5. The stud was conducted on 1.1M persons above 60 years of age at least 12 days after the booster shot and at least 5 months after the second shot.
[Cancer] Weighing cancer cells to personalize drug choices
